before this court.

19:53.640 --> 19:55.711
- They're making an example of
me, that's what they're doing.

19:55.780 --> 19:57.126
- It's exactly
what they're doing.

19:57.196 --> 19:59.232
And we need to let them,
just a little.

19:59.301 --> 20:01.476
Because there's
no jury of your peers here.

20:01.545 --> 20:02.960
Your peers are in Portland.

20:03.029 --> 20:04.858
And in Portland,
he may be the enemy

20:04.927 --> 20:07.067
or I may be the enemy, but here?

20:07.136 --> 20:09.794
The enemy is you.

20:09.863 --> 20:11.762
We don't want
to go before a jury.

20:11.831 --> 20:13.591
Let me go try
and plea this down.

20:16.491 --> 20:18.631
- Can I talk to him
for a minute, please?

20:18.700 --> 20:19.666
- I'll be outside.

20:27.571 --> 20:29.193
- I can't believe
this is happening.

20:29.262 --> 20:33.232
- Yeah.
Well, it's happening.

20:35.441 --> 20:38.202
- Do you know the judge?
- I know the judge.

20:38.271 --> 20:39.755
- Can you talk to him?

20:39.824 --> 20:43.759
- Let's...
Let's save that card.

20:44.795 --> 20:47.107
- They're asking for life.

20:47.176 --> 20:48.281
- That'll come down.

20:48.350 --> 20:50.456
- To what? 30 years?

20:50.525 --> 20:53.148
I'm going to do
three decades in prison?

20:53.217 --> 20:54.598
My God, I mean...

