I don't care.

41:32.869 --> 41:34.388
I don't care
if she dies in prison.

41:34.457 --> 41:37.874
I don't care if she gets out,
I do not fucking care, okay?

41:37.943 --> 41:39.704
I care about you,
I care about Kayce,

41:39.773 --> 41:41.499
I care about Rip.

41:43.052 --> 41:44.916
- Well, if you care about them
then you need to care

41:44.985 --> 41:46.952
about having some morality
in the way you fight.

41:49.437 --> 41:51.819
- There's no such thing.
Not in a kingdom.

41:51.888 --> 41:53.821
And that's what this is.

41:53.890 --> 41:57.376
There is no morality
here, Dad, none.

41:57.445 --> 42:00.448
There is keep the kingdom
or there is lose the kingdom.

42:00.518 --> 42:02.727
Or break your
fucking promise, Dad.

42:02.796 --> 42:05.868
Break it and sell this place.

42:05.937 --> 42:08.111
Take the money,
buy up half of Oklahoma

42:08.180 --> 42:10.389
and run cattle for
the next 20 generations

42:10.458 --> 42:13.151
where no one gives a fuck
about you or your land.

42:14.186 --> 42:16.982
- My kingdom, my rules.

42:17.051 --> 42:19.744
We fight with dignity.
You aren't.

42:19.813 --> 42:21.815
You start or find another fight.

42:24.645 --> 42:26.440
- What does that mean?

42:26.509 --> 42:28.856
- I'm saying no more collateral
damage, you understand me?

42:30.409 --> 42:33.551
We don't kill sheep.
We kill wolves.

42:35.518 --> 42:37.693
What you did was cruel, honey.

42:37.762 --> 42:39.418
- Because you fucked her,
it's cruel?

42:39.487 --> 42:41.904
- Did you do it
because I fucked her?

42:43.561 --> 42:44.976
Because that is cruel.

42:46.115 --> 42:47.703
Goddam, Beth, I never
thought I'd feel

42:47.772 --> 42:49.394
this way about you before,

42:49.463 --> 42:53.225
but you have really
disappointed me, honey.

42:53.294 --> 42:55.365
And I never thought
I'd say that about you.

42:59.438 --> 43:00.716
- Me neither.

43:05.237 --> 43:09.656
- You know, maybe it's best
if I fight this alone.

43:09.725 --> 43:11.312
Maybe it's best if you
go somewhere else

43:11.381 --> 43:12.486
while I do it.

43:14.281 --> 43:15.593
- This is my home.

43:18.492 --> 43:20.183
- Might be time
to find another one.

43:51.076 --> 43:52.526
- Got 'em all sorted, huh?

43:52.595 --> 43:54.424
- Yep.

43:54.493 --> 43:57.013
- Sale's done?
- Yep.

44:00.189 --> 44:03.054
- Goodbyes are too hard, Jimmy.
That's why I said it quick.

44:03.123 --> 44:05.021
Let's not do this.

44:05.090 --> 44:07.575
- I'm not saying goodbye.

44:07.645 --> 44:08.956
I'm keeping you.

44:11.200 --> 44:13.029
I'll day work, I'll do
what I have to do.

44:13.098 --> 44:15.894
- Can't let you break
your word over me.

44:15.963 --> 44:18.103
It'll be the thing that breaks
us, then you'll have nothing.

44:20.830 --> 44:23.143
Keep your word.

44:23.212 --> 44:24.316
Then come back to me.

44:29.080 --> 44:30.840
If you ask me to wait,
I'll wait...

44:30.909 --> 44:32.255
- Wait for me.

44:33.912 --> 44:35.120
- Okay.

44:36.708 --> 44:41.886
♪ There's a scar
on my soul ♪

44:41.955 --> 44:46.200
♪ So let me down easy ♪

44:46.269 --> 44:50.860
♪ Break my heart sweetly ♪

44:50.929 --> 44:53.518
♪ Like you always do ♪

45:00.732 --> 45:03.045
- ♪ One-night stand
in Mississippi ♪

45:03.114 --> 45:04.460
♪ Final leg... ♪

45:04.529 --> 45:06.013
- Look at this fucking kid.
He's done this before.

45:06.082 --> 45:07.325
- My first time.

45:07.394 --> 45:09.430
- You're shuffling the cards
in the air.

45:09.499 --> 45:11.122
- First time actually playing.

45:12.606 --> 45:14.435
- Hey.
- All right.

45:16.334 --> 45:18.163
♪ Singing songs
along the highway ♪

45:18.232 --> 45:19.337
Triple it.

45:19.406 --> 45:21.063
- Triple the bet he says?

45:22.202 --> 45:23.479
- Madman.

45:23.548 --> 45:25.723
- This little card shark
motherfuckin' kid.

45:25.792 --> 45:28.553
- Hay ain't no kid, he's just
a motherfucking card sharkin'--

45:28.622 --> 45:30.003
little elf.

45:30.072 --> 45:31.107
- You tell him, baby.

45:31.176 --> 45:32.350
- I love it when
you call me baby.

45:32.419 --> 45:34.110
You want to scratch
me behind my ears?

45:34.179 --> 45:35.387
- No.
- What about my other ears?

45:35.456 --> 45:38.045
- Don't listen, just start.

45:38.114 --> 45:39.737
- Get a room, you guys.

45:39.806 --> 45:41.359
- Here's the flop.
- The flop?

45:41.428 --> 45:42.843
- He knows the terminology.

45:42.912 --> 45:45.052
What, did you buy him
at a fucking circus?

45:45.121 --> 45:46.813
Poker circus?
That's disrespectful.

45:46.882 --> 45:48.987
- Come on, boy.
There you go.

45:49.056 --> 45:51.541
I love it.
- Do you know what he has?

45:51.610 --> 45:53.164
- Don't you worry.
- All right.

45:53.233 --> 45:54.648
- All right, well...
- Check.

45:54.717 --> 45:58.272
- Ain't no checking today.

45:58.341 --> 46:00.136
- Oh.
- Fuck off.

46:00.205 --> 46:02.483
- Come on, son.

46:02.552 --> 46:05.555
- It's down to the kid
and the unluckiest card player
on earth now.

46:05.624 --> 46:07.626
- I wonder how
that's gonna work out.

46:07.695 --> 46:09.697
- Do we, though?

46:09.767 --> 46:12.183
All right,
he got something.

46:12.252 --> 46:13.356
- And the river.

46:13.425 --> 46:15.117
- You're fucked, kid.

46:15.186 --> 46:16.635
- Are you alive on the river?

46:16.704 --> 46:18.120
- Look who's back.

46:21.709 --> 46:22.780
- You look awful sad.

46:24.126 --> 46:25.161
- Yeah, I am.

46:26.507 --> 46:28.406
- How come?

46:28.475 --> 46:30.270
- I just lost the one thing

46:30.339 --> 46:31.927
I've spent my entire life
fighting for.

46:34.170 --> 46:36.034
I'm wondering what
else it's gonna cost me.

46:40.245 --> 46:41.453
Do you know any sad songs?

46:42.661 --> 46:44.146
- Most people say that's
all I know.

46:48.598 --> 46:49.945
- Would you play one for me?

46:52.879 --> 46:54.087
- Yeah, I can do that.

46:54.156 --> 46:55.260
What, you got boat?

46:55.329 --> 46:57.297
- Listen to this
fucking kid, boat.

46:57.366 --> 46:59.437
- He's a cheating
little squirrely haired

46:59.506 --> 47:01.888
little twat mouth
cunt motherfucking

47:01.957 --> 47:04.097
face of death nose.

47:04.166 --> 47:05.995
- What's wrong with her?
- What do you mean?

47:06.064 --> 47:07.790
- She bite off
her tongue or something?

47:09.240 --> 47:11.069
- Fuck you!
Don't laugh at that shit.

47:15.246 --> 47:16.764
- What's so fucking
funny back there?

47:16.834 --> 47:20.113
- He's kicking your ass and
talking shit at the same time.

47:20.182 --> 47:21.666
- Pot's right.
Let's do it.

47:21.735 --> 47:24.669
- Yeah, that's right. I do have
the boat you little bastard.

47:24.738 --> 47:28.328
Aces up.
- Oh!

47:28.397 --> 47:30.537
It's your bedtime.
- So did I.

47:30.606 --> 47:31.745
- Oh!

47:33.505 --> 47:36.439
- The same exact cards
last time.

47:40.616 --> 47:43.205
- If you're so sad, how about
I play you something happy?

47:46.415 --> 47:49.107
- No. I need to cry.

47:52.559 --> 47:54.941
But I'm incapable
of crying for myself.

47:55.010 --> 47:58.151
Walker, I need a song
to cry to.

48:01.637 --> 48:04.709
- This is about a man
who got killed that...

48:04.778 --> 48:05.883
wasn't quite ready to die.

48:07.850 --> 48:11.923
Guess as his soul
was floating up in the air

48:11.992 --> 48:15.754
he's looking down on all
the things he was gonna miss.

48:15.823 --> 48:17.722
Pretty sure he cried.

48:20.518 --> 48:22.485
- Yeah, that sounds
like a song for me.

48:39.778 --> 48:43.403
♪ The other day I found
myself up on the corner ♪

48:43.472 --> 48:47.510
♪ I thought I run into
a friend of mine ♪

48:47.579 --> 48:50.893
♪ Ended up he was
just a stranger ♪

48:50.962 --> 48:53.551
♪ Said hello
and he passed me by ♪

49:01.248 --> 49:04.665
♪ But then he turned
and put a gun to my head ♪

49:04.734 --> 49:08.704
♪ He said my friend,
I'm gonna rob you blind ♪

49:08.773 --> 49:11.741
♪ I said you must be
down on your luck ♪

49:11.810 --> 49:15.124
♪ I'm outta money
and I'm all out of time ♪

49:30.070 --> 49:33.418
♪ He pulled the trigger
and I fell to my knees ♪

49:33.487 --> 49:35.869
♪ My spirit left
and then my body went cold ♪

49:37.319 --> 49:40.391
♪ I'm looking down upon
the lights of the city ♪

49:40.460 --> 49:43.981
♪ I feel alive
but I'm dead and gone ♪

49:57.063 --> 49:59.997
♪ Ain't no more favors
from someone I don't know ♪

50:00.066 --> 50:02.206
♪ 'Cause there ain't
nobody hear me ♪

50:02.275 --> 50:04.104
♪ Nobody's around ♪

50:06.072 --> 50:09.972
♪ Hallelujah ♪

50:10.041 --> 50:11.525
♪ He's dead and gone ♪

50:13.803 --> 50:16.565
♪ Hallelujah ♪

50:24.538 --> 50:28.094
- Do I have to go up
on the hill too?

50:28.163 --> 50:29.371
- Some day.

50:29.440 --> 50:31.649
- When?

50:31.718 --> 50:32.719
- When your heart tells you to.

50:35.411 --> 50:36.964
- Right here, Tate.

51:06.787 --> 51:07.892
- Gotta be honest.

51:10.481 --> 51:12.483
Not sure I believe
in all this.

51:12.552 --> 51:14.140
- It sure believes in you.

51:15.969 --> 51:17.522
Hey...

51:17.591 --> 51:19.662
Wherever something
good's trying to happen

51:19.731 --> 51:21.940
something bad is trying
to stop it.

51:22.009 --> 51:24.978
Your only safe place
is inside your prayer ties.

51:26.152 --> 51:27.774
Your only protection
is the pipe.

51:31.433 --> 51:34.160
Everything else
around you could be evil.

51:35.747 --> 51:40.476
Beware the coyote, he is the
trickster and cannot be trusted.

51:42.133 --> 51:43.169
- How long is Hanbleceya?

51:44.377 --> 51:46.068
- Four days
and four nights.

51:46.137 --> 51:48.691
No food.
No water.

51:50.348 --> 51:51.591
- No water?

51:51.660 --> 51:53.386
- None.

51:53.455 --> 51:54.870
- I'll die.

51:54.939 --> 51:56.975
- You must stand
on the cliff of death

51:57.044 --> 52:00.669
to understand
your purpose in life.

52:00.738 --> 52:02.740
It's the only place
where you can see it.

52:13.682 --> 52:15.097
She's a good woman.

52:17.858 --> 52:19.032
- Better than I deserve.

52:20.067 --> 52:22.449
- God doesn't work like that.

52:22.518 --> 52:25.521
He would never let her love
someone who didn't deserve her.

53:12.844 --> 53:14.191
- I feel kinda silly.

53:15.468 --> 53:17.366
- Listen to Mo.

53:17.435 --> 53:19.610
Do what he says
exactly as he says it.

53:22.440 --> 53:23.786
I love you.

53:31.277 --> 53:32.623
- See you in a few days.

54:50.563 --> 54:53.428
Use the sage to keep
bad spirits off.

54:53.497 --> 54:56.293
Use the sweet grass to call
your spirit helpers in.

54:57.570 --> 55:00.193
Smoke the pipe when you pray.
Understand?

55:03.196 --> 55:06.372
- You'll be surprised
how quickly you'll replay

55:06.441 --> 55:09.306
all your moments
in life in your mind.

55:09.375 --> 55:11.860
And then what?

55:11.929 --> 55:16.140
When you are without memories,
without regrets to ponder,

55:16.209 --> 55:20.938
without fantasies
to embrace or to reject,

55:21.007 --> 55:23.837
what will you think of then?

55:23.906 --> 55:26.737
What will come to you depends

55:26.806 --> 55:30.568
on how hard you pray
and how much you suffer.

55:32.432 --> 55:33.847
Close him in, Mo.

55:50.312 --> 55:51.865
- How will you know
when I'm done?

55:53.142 --> 55:54.765
- How will you know, Kayce?

55:57.319 --> 55:58.562
That is the question.
